{"word":"H6571 - פָּרָשׁ - pârâsh - paw-rawsh' - Horseman","slug":"H6571","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">פָּרָשׁ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>pârâsh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>paw-rawsh'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Horseman"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E4;&#x05BC;&#x05E8;&#x05E9;&#x05C1; - pa&#x0302;ra&#x0302;sh</b> - <i>paw-rawsh'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H6567\">H6567</a>; a <i>steed</i> (as <i>stretched</i> out to a vehicle, not single nor for mounting (compare <a href=\"#/H5483\">H5483</a>)); also (by implication) a <i>driver</i> (in a chariot), that is, (collectively) cavalry: - horseman."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6572\">H6572</a>, <a href=\"#/H6574\">H6574</a>, <a href=\"#/H6577\">H6577</a>, <a href=\"#/H6578\">H6578</a>, <a href=\"#/H6579\">H6579</a>"}]}